of older brother or male.]

189
00:15:47,104 --> 00:15:48,744
I'm only gullible with you.

190
00:15:50,124 --> 00:15:51,204
Is that so?

191
00:15:52,544 --> 00:15:53,484
Gaebong.

192
00:15:54,824 --> 00:15:58,304
What are you thinking about?

193
00:15:58,304 --> 00:16:00,594
What are you imagining about?

194
00:16:00,594 --> 00:16:03,064
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

195
00:16:09,284 --> 00:16:10,464
Gaebong.

196
00:16:10,944 --> 00:16:12,804
Everything is almost done.

197
00:16:13,024 --> 00:16:15,384
Just hold on a little longer.

198
00:16:16,124 --> 00:16:20,404
I'll return everything
to where it once was.

199
00:16:20,874 --> 00:16:22,814
Don't you trust me?

200
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:25,624
I do.

201
00:16:27,044 --> 00:16:29,784
- It just feels weird.
- What does?

202
00:16:31,464 --> 00:16:34,704
It's the first time
someone's said to me,

203
00:16:35,524 --> 00:16:37,204
“Don't worry,” “Trust me.”

204
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:41,064
and “I'll take care of it.”

205
00:16:41,944 --> 00:16:44,364
I always used to say that.

206
00:16:44,704 --> 00:16:46,824
Weren't the weight of those words

207
00:16:47,334 --> 00:16:49,004
quite heavy?

208
00:16:49,924 --> 00:16:51,964
They were heavy at times,

209
00:16:52,624 --> 00:16:54,984
But thinking that
I could protect my people

210
00:16:54,984 --> 00:16:57,644
on my own,

211
00:16:58,144 --> 00:16:59,784
I was happy.

212
00:17:01,344 --> 00:17:04,264
So whenever there was a problem,

213
00:17:04,264 --> 00:17:05,964
I found a solution.

214
00:17:08,954 --> 00:17:10,404
But this time,

215
00:17:11,084 --> 00:17:12,524
I just can't find a way.

216
00:17:12,924 --> 00:17:14,104
No.

217
00:17:14,584 --> 00:17:16,804
I know there is a way,

218
00:17:17,584 --> 00:17:21,984
but I can't decide

219
00:17:23,724 --> 00:17:25,444
if I should keep going or give up.

220
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:31,064
That's why you can't
scratch your own back.

221
00:17:32,344 --> 00:17:33,584
What?

222
00:17:33,584 --> 00:17:35,854
Didn't you say that to me before?

223
00:17:36,204 --> 00:17:37,984
When you have a lot on your mind,

224
00:17:37,984 --> 00:17:40,624
it's best to simply make calculations.

225
00:17:40,884 --> 00:17:42,424
Make calculations?

226
00:17:43,024 --> 00:17:43,924
What do you mean?

227
00:17:43,924 --> 00:17:46,104
Compare the pros and the cons,

228
00:17:46,624 --> 00:17:48,364
and choose the pros.

229
00:17:50,084 --> 00:17:52,424
You already know the answer,

230
00:17:52,424 --> 00:17:55,064
you don't need to complicate things.

231
00:17:56,364 --> 00:17:59,744
Seeing your expression,
it seems you've found the solution.

232
00:18:00,764 --> 00:18:02,524
Now that I'm thinking about the pros,

233
00:18:02,524 --> 00:18:04,364
I think I can see a way.

234
00:18:04,364 --> 00:18:09,144
But what if I can't
compare the pros and cons?

235
00:18:09,484 --> 00:18:11,904
Aren't you a trader, Gaebong?

236
00:18:12,654 --> 00:18:15,744
Then there should be
a standard for traders.

237
00:18:16,204 --> 00:18:18,164
You just need to follow that.

238
00:18:19,024 --> 00:18:21,524
Do you really think so?

239
00:18:21,844 --> 00:18:23,734
Of course, I think so.

240
00:18:25,734 --> 00:18:27,234
Thank you for understanding.

241
00:18:27,624 --> 00:18:29,164
You brat.

242
00:18:30,464 --> 00:18:33,004
Then you may leave now.

243
00:18:33,844 --> 00:18:34,944
You want me to leave?

244
00:18:34,944 --> 00:18:36,644
I can't walk you out.

245
00:18:36,644 --> 00:18:38,074
I have work to do.

246
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:40,004
Wait.

247
00:18:40,744 --> 00:18:42,044
Hey, Gaebong!

248
00:18:42,044 --> 00:18:43,364
Gaebong!

249
00:18:44,854 --> 00:18:46,984
That brat.

250
00:18:51,024 --> 00:18:52,544
Thank you

251
00:18:53,324 --> 00:18:56,684
for always being by my side.

252
00:18:57,924 --> 00:18:59,204
Thank you.

253
00:19:04,584 --> 00:19:06,784
Oh man, we were alone in this room.

254
00:19:24,224 --> 00:19:26,464
- Father!
- My son!

255
00:19:27,924 --> 00:19:29,344
Okay, okay.

256
00:19:29,344 --> 00:19:31,484
Welcome back.

257
00:19:32,224 --> 00:19:34,104
- Have you been well?
- Yes.

258
00:19:34,104 --> 00:19:35,644
I've been well, Father.

259
00:19:37,324 --> 00:19:42,344
Tomorrow, I'll give
a requisition order at the meeting.

260
00:19:42,344 --> 00:19:46,204
We must admit all men
to compulsory service,

261
00:19:46,564 --> 00:19:49,624
so that we won't run into a problem
with the move to the west.

262
00:19:49,624 --> 00:19:50,644
Yes.

263
00:19:51,004 --> 00:19:53,504
I know very well what I must do, Father.

264
00:19:53,504 --> 00:19:56,154
I'm so proud of you.

265
00:19:57,804 --> 00:19:59,024
Yes.

266
00:20:00,384 --> 00:20:05,624
You must be tired from
your long journey here, General Gwak.

267
00:20:10,944 --> 00:20:12,044
Here, here.

268
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,284
Sit down.

269
00:20:16,764 --> 00:20:18,944
How long has it been?

270
00:20:19,164 --> 00:20:21,644
It's the first time
we've seen one another

271
00:20:22,044 --> 00:20:24,484
since we defeated the Khitans.

272
00:20:26,704 --> 00:20:32,454
I'm still alive because
you fought with us.

273
